  <h1>Contact</h1>
  <time datetime=2019-09-21T00:00:00-0500 class="post-date">Sat, Sep 21, 2019</time>
  <p>I used to be hesitant about contacting people on the web. My caution was
misplaced. All of them turned out to be nice people.</p>

<p>I suspect that I&rsquo;m not alone in this, so here&rsquo;s my offer: *if you want
to talk to me, I want to talk to you.*Â  You can contact me at robb at rs
dot io.</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>I like receiving email from real people.</strong> There has never been a time
when I found myself thinking, &ldquo;Wow, I wish I received fewer thoughtful
emails from flesh and blood humans.&rdquo; If I ever do get to that point, I
will hire a secretary. Email is amazing. Someone from rural China can
send me a message within seconds, for free, and I can reply, for free!</li>
<li><strong>I like hearing about what my readers are up to.</strong> If you&rsquo;re working on
a project and would like me to check it out, or need some feedback, I
would like to hear from you. Send me a link.</li>
<li><strong>I like reading.</strong> I spend a lot of my time reading about stuff. If
you&rsquo;ve written something you think I&rsquo;d enjoy, please send it to me. If
you&rsquo;ve read a great book recently, recommend it to me. I love book
recommendations. If you think there&rsquo;s an article that needs more
exposure or that I&rsquo;d enjoy, send it to me.</li>
<li><strong>I like self-promotion.</strong> If you created something, and you&rsquo;re proud of
it, please tell me about!</li>
<li><strong>I like helping people out.</strong> If you need assistance with something, I
would like to help you. If I can make the world a little better one
email at a time, I&rsquo;ll do so.</li>
</ul>

<p>You can reach me at robb at rs dot io.</p>

